  "raw_text": "die; the mind builds in a death strip. Its usefulness as Flux is over (decreed as over). This is a totally determined moment. The permutating ontogon is totally expendable - which is a tragedy, an absolute tragedy. To the mind, any & all ontogons have no purpose except to generate the phylogon. But Xtianity has sabotaged this process by editing the death strip (1) out of existence, & by drawing in the phylogon for the use of the ontogon, reversing the normal means-end relationship. (1) of the given ontogon folder 49 - 128 folder 49 - 128 Note from p 1129 : \"Rest.\" The ontogon sits still as accretional layer after accretional layer is laid down & the phylogon is formed along this axis. There are billions of phylogons. The mind really doesn't see anything but phylogons. \"King Felix\" _when printed_ became a phylogon : & the mind could see it. Ontogons are not information. Phylogons are. To the mind, ontogons are simply process, a mechanism. But is the sheep dream educating me further along the lines of the James-James dream? Because this is a serious matter : the torture & killing of the ontogons in order to produce the phylogons. Plato is unaware of this, that the \"shadows\" of the forms must be first contoured & then destroyed in order to bring into existence the phylogons. I have not figured this out; I have been shown this. & I have been shown that the suffering of the ontogons is of more spiritual significance than the purpose they serve : the Beauty of their given phylogon. I think it very likely that \"Thomas\" was indeed the phylogenic mind (of the human species) & that he is Christ; which is to say, Christ is the phylogon of which we are the ontogons. Hence the vast space & time, & memories of First Century A.D. Palestine & fear of the Romans & the Koine. Here is a unique phylogon. Not only is it supra human but it is interested in extricating human ontogons from their torment & death strips, & enabling them to participate in the phylogon's immortality folder 49 - 129 folder 49 - 129 This is the greater revolution in the history of reality, because otherwise the ontogons always serve [in the role of bringing into existence] the phylogons, & are intrinsically expendable under the conditions of pain & death. Thus I distinguish the mind Valis from Thomas; Valis is the system & would be Xenophanes' Nous & Spinoza's Deus. However, Christos & Theos are not antithetical. (1) But they are different. (1) I wonder. These are hard sayings. What indeed as the sheep dream & the James-James dream imply, Christ has revolted against Theos, & Theos has no concern for ontogons. Then we have Gnosticism & Mani! Christ = the rule of Mercy. Theos = Justice (sic). Or are we simply to regard Christ as an instrument by which the distribution between ontogon & phylogon is abolished? No; in the sheep dream I said, \"May they be damned to hell\" referring to the system by which ontogons are tormented & killed to produce the best phylogon. Is this the system of \"the Law\"? It is the basis of reality & Christ has revolted against it, & this news has been smuggled in to _me_, into the Prison (\"Tears\"). The system is a vast slave prison for us ontogons. & Christ enters from outside, exactly as Gnosticism teaches; & esoteric knowledge is involved : this is what is being revealed to me. folder 49 - 130 folder 49 - 130 The Xtianity is a revolt against the Torah information system & The Prime Mind itself, the Spinoza Deus. & this is exactly what the Gnostics taught : Christ vs the Creator, & this is esoteric understanding \"Evil holds all the centers. There Xtianity is illegal & underground.\" I mean, I'm not figuring this out; it's being revealed to me. We're dealing with a secret society like the Rosy Cross. We're dealing with (1) the basic original total Torah system is bad because in producing the phylogons (which _are_ admittedly beautiful in the sense of Pythagoras' Kosmos, the ultimate Greek concept of beauty) it torments & kills the ontogons; & (2) there is a revolt against this because of this fact : the torment & killing outweighs - Yes, outweighs - the positive value of Kosmos. _It is Agape vs Pythagoras' Kosmos._!! These two absolute values clash head-on. Theos = Kosmos. Christos = Agape. This is the dramatic & tragic collision (cf conceptions of tragedy). Could it by Dionysos (Agape) against Apollo (Kosmos)? It is so strange because what we have here is the specific issue - collision - of \"Chains of Air\"! & Christ is mentioned. Is it possible that a phylogon so evolved has come into existence that it seeks to rescue the ontogons that make it up? a unique phylogon? which means that this revolt was planned by folder 49 - 131 the very mind of the system (Theos) from the start? So here we have again the \"Secret Partnership\"? _This_ phylogon subordinates itself to [the needs of] its own ontogons? Voluntarily? (no other phylogon does so; this is the phylogon of phylogons.) (&, as such, abases itself to its meanest ontogons!) Something of a dramatic paradox is involved, here; the ultimate phylogon, which by definition is the goal of all ontogons, abases itself to the service of the ontogons required by the system to expend & sacrifice themselves for it; it sacrifices itself for them! Yet this very paradox is found in both Xtianity & in Buddhism! It's like a vast polarity reversal of the total system : means-end, inner-outer, upper-lower, larger-smaller, whole-part, a looping back into opposites. Like a snake swallowing its tail. The pyramid ends at it pinnacle with the divine which then ascends to re-enter at the bottom layer (v. \"Ubik\" & the divine at the trash level). The evolutionary dialectical process culminates with Christ ?? - then penetrates the lowest level; i.e. the next level up from the most exalted - spiritual - beautiful - meaningful is - the lowest trash layer! This is a revelation that logic can't disclose. Yet it appears in \"Ubik\" & \"Chains of Air\"! The path leads up from the Mahler 2nd to Ghandi cleaning a toilet; this is a mystery; some kind of further metamorphosis takes place, a conversion back (?) to the bottom. Then in that case the bottom layer is the place to seek the divine, logically (& paradoxically). Since it is higher than the spiritual. folder 49 - 132 folder 49 - 132 This is certainly the idea in \"Chains of Air\"! It's sort of the final extension of the Theophany at Mt. Horeb : the low murmuring voice. \"What's the _next_ step? What's the _final_ step?\" In this way all creation is knit together (view it as a hexagram). The light passes out at the top & then returns at the bottom. Consider Pinky. He was crazy, crapping on the floor, sick & dirty - & turned into a being of unsurpassed spiritual beauty. There is some kind of logic to this; it has to do with conversion into opposites, & with latent form. I've got to consider 3-74 an _example_ of this conversion! I had descended to the bottom layer of reality in terms of spiritual value; & then an alchemical \"lead-into-gold\" occurred in me! as an ontogon of Christ I sure wasn't much. This whole system (logic) isn't arbitrary, but it's a logic you can only see & understand in retrospect. I am talking about _why me_. (i.e. a cause-&-effect basis, a Theodecy of Pronoia). I've been shown a really perplexing paradox. The highest good is the \"harmonious-fitting-together of the beautiful -i.e. Pythagoras' Kosmos & this is what Theos moves everything & process towards. Okay. & then I've been shown the cost at which this is achieved - the torture & killing of folder 49 - 133 folder 49 - 133 the epicreatures, & I am shown that this cost is too great! So the summum bonum can only be achieved at a cost that (spiritually speaking) makes it not worth it (i.e. unacceptable). Then is the summum bonum actually the summum bonum? How can it be? Isn't there a logical contradiction here? Right : there sure is! This is the dramatic tragedy of the universe, of God, of all process, reality & goal (teleology). Okay, then the _real_ summum bonum lies in saving the epicreatures (i.e. the parts which go together to make the whole.) The whole is _not_ greater than the sum of its parts; no; each & every part (ontogon) is more important than the whole! So within the summum bonum there is a _secret_. A mysterious conversion occurs. The part is the _real_ whole; the phylogon is the ontogon & vice versa. Perhaps this is an umreconciliable Irish bull which sets off the infinite flip flop, of the dialectic; maybe _this_ particular paradox is the primal imbalance that is the dynamism driving reality on || \\\\ || \\\\ forever; it can not _ever_ be resolved, so process never ends (which is good). Maybe the ultimate paradox underlying process reality per se has been revealed to me. It can be defined folder 49 - 134 folder 49 - 134 logically this way : Q : What is the goal (purpose) of all reality? A : The harmonious fitting together of everything (every part) into the unitary beautiful. Q : How is this done? A : Tormenting & killing the many ephemeral parts. Q : Is this justified? A : No. Q : Then is the Summum Bonum justified? A : No; there is a higher value than the Summum Bonum. It is the extrication of the suffering parts. Q : Then the initial answer is false. A : No, it is true; it is a postulate. (out of _this_ the dialectic which never ends is initiated. This here is the dramatic tragic story which our world can be reduced to; it is our world's tale.) Solution : the mind (??? Theos) MUST create a counter-entity which will work for the extrication of the parts at the expense of the whole. Thus the Godhead is ipso facto divided & pitted against itself. It assumes an antithetical interaction with itself, part (half) of folder 49 - 135 folder 49 - 135 if the Godhead works synthetically, to fit everything together harmoniously into an integrated whole (Kosmos) & half works to assist & rescue the epiparts subjected to stress, torment & death in the pursuit of the above goal. Hence the Godhead is in infinite crisis, a push-pull binary dialectic is created, & this is _exactly_ what was revealed to me as the basis - not just of reality - but of the Godhead itself, the practical result is that everything is perpetually (dynamically) converted into its opposite. & this ur-paradox in the macrocosm has mirrored effects in every micro form down throughout creation! (v Taoism!) In terms of the evolution of awareness, the total system advances. Through stages, (1) until it becomes aware of the cost, hence the paradox, then splits into antithetical halves & remains in this dynamic balance state forever, or else repeats the cycle again & again forever. (1) in promoting Pythagoras' Kosmos as God. Then Kosmos can only be a theoretic goal; in actuality it can never be achieved because it involves a self-contradiction (the cost); empathy arises & having arisen grows - defeating Kosmos. Prognosis. Continual growth of empathy in the system as it evolves - & away from its proper (original) goal. The totality voluntarily decomposes it own psychosoma folder 49 - 136 Thus the rupture in the Godhead was _necessary_, given its (the Godhead's) drive to complete itself as Kosmos). It was driven inexorably to this schism; hence the one became two, & the dialectic came into existence. As it became increasingly aware,",
