  "evidence_excerpts": [
    {
      "text": "Last edit about 9 years ago by erica snowlake\n\nfolder 49 - 131\nthe very mind of the system (Theos) from the start? So here we have again the \"Secret Partnership\"? _This_ phylogon subordinates itself to [the needs of] its own ontogons? Voluntarily? (no other phylogon does so; this is the phylogon of phylogons.) (&, as such, abases itself to its meanest ontogons!) Something of a dramatic paradox is involved, here; the ultimate phylogon, which by definition is the goal of all ontogons, abases itsel",
      "matched_alias": "Buddhism",
      "term_id": "TERM_buddhism",
      "term_name": "Buddhism",
      "term_slug": "buddhism"
    },
    {
      "text": "Last edit about 9 years ago by erica snowlake\nfolder 49 - 129\nComplete\nfolder 49 - 129\nThis is the greater revolution in the history of reality, because otherwise the ontogons always serve [in the role of bringing into existence] the phylogons, & are intrinsically expendable under the conditions of pain & death. Thus I distinguish the mind Valis from Thomas; Valis is the system & would be Xenophanes' Nous & Spinoza's Deus.\n\nHowever, Christos & Theos are not antithetical. (1) But they are differe",
      "matched_alias": "Nous",
      "term_id": "TERM_nous",
      "term_name": "Nous",
      "term_slug": "nous"
    }
  ],
